atmpAgentType.name: atmpAgentType
atmpAgentType.description: The type of ATMP HA Agent. ha-router means the HA will route the tunneled data to other networks. ha-gateway means the HA delivers tunneled data to other networks without routing anything. A ha-notapp will be returned for FA and if ATMP is disabled.

atmpAgentUDPPort.name: atmpAgentUDPPort
atmpAgentUDPPort.description: UDP port number to be used for ATMP.

atmpAgentGreMtu.name: atmpAgentGreMtu
atmpAgentGreMtu.description: The maximum IP packet size that can be transmitted to a peer agent without performing fragmentation. The value 0 means this feature is disabled.

atmpAgentForceFragmentation.name: atmpAgentForceFragmentation
atmpAgentForceFragmentation.description: To force fragmentation of large IP frames before they are sent to the peer agent even if the packet has the DF bit set. NOTE: this behavior is not standard and prevents MTU discovery mechanisms. This works in conjunction with atmpAgentGreMtu.

atmpAgentHAIdleLimit.name: atmpAgentHAIdleLimit
atmpAgentHAIdleLimit.description: Time in minutes that the HA will allow a tunnel to have no traffic before tearing it down. The value 0 means this option is disabled.

atmpLastErrorGenerated.name: atmpLastErrorGenerated
atmpLastErrorGenerated.description: This is the last error at the Agent level or Tunnel creation that was generated by the Agent. To clear the field and atmpAgentSentErrorTo do a set with the value no-error(1)

atmpAgentSentErrorTo.name: atmpAgentSentErrorTo
atmpAgentSentErrorTo.description: The IP Address of the agent that the generated was sent to. Clearing atmpLastErrorGenerated also clears this field.

atmpLastErrorRecv.name: atmpLastErrorRecv
atmpLastErrorRecv.description: This is the last error at the Agent level or Tunnel creation that was received from the Peer Agent. To clear the field and atmpAgentRecvErrorFrom do a set with the value no-error(1)

atmpAgentRecvErrorFrom.name: atmpAgentRecvErrorFrom
atmpAgentRecvErrorFrom.description: The IP Address of the agent that the last error received was from. Clearing atmpLastErrorRecv also clears this field.

atmpAgentNumberLocalTunnels.name: atmpAgentNumberLocalTunnels
atmpAgentNumberLocalTunnels.description: The number of Local client mode tunnels.

atmpAgentTunnelHighWater.name: atmpAgentTunnelHighWater
atmpAgentTunnelHighWater.description: The high water mark on created ATMP tunnels.

atmpTunnelTable.name: atmpTunnelTable
atmpTunnelTable.description: A list of ATMP tunnel entries.

atmpTunnelIndex.name: atmpTunnelIndex
atmpTunnelIndex.description: A unique index assigned to this tunnel.

atmpTunnelId.name: atmpTunnelId
atmpTunnelId.description: The tunnel ID assigned to this tunnel. This number is assigned by the HA. NOTE: this number does *not* uniquely identify a tunnel.

atmpHAIpAddress.name: atmpHAIpAddress
atmpHAIpAddress.description: The IP Address of this tunnel's HA.

atmpFAIpAddress.name: atmpFAIpAddress
atmpFAIpAddress.description: The IP Address of this tunnel's FA.

atmpTunneledProtocol.name: atmpTunneledProtocol
atmpTunneledProtocol.description: This value indicates the protocol(s) that the tunnel supports. The value is a sum. The sum initially takes the value zero. Then for each protocol that is supported, the value of the protocol is or'ed to the sum. Example: 3 means ip and ipx.

atmpTunnelType.name: atmpTunnelType
atmpTunnelType.description: The type of tunnel this is.

atmpTunnelState.name: atmpTunnelState
atmpTunnelState.description: These are the states the tunnel can be in.

atmpMnIpAddress.name: atmpMnIpAddress
atmpMnIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Mobile Node.

atmpMnNetmask.name: atmpMnNetmask
atmpMnNetmask.description: The netmask of the Mobile Node.

atmpMnIpxNetAddress.name: atmpMnIpxNetAddress
atmpMnIpxNetAddress.description: The IPX network address of the Mobile Node.

atmpMnIpxNodeAddress.name: atmpMnIpxNodeAddress
atmpMnIpxNodeAddress.description: The IPX node address of the Mobile Node.

atmpHNProfileName.name: atmpHNProfileName
atmpHNProfileName.description: The name of the home network profile which will be used to forward all packets received by the HA. This may be NULL if the HA is in router mode.

atmpHNMaxTunnels.name: atmpHNMaxTunnels
atmpHNMaxTunnels.description: The maximum number of tunnels allowed to this HN.

atmpFAPrimaryHAAddress.name: atmpFAPrimaryHAAddress
atmpFAPrimaryHAAddress.description: The Address of the Primary HA. This is known on the FA and will be NULL if the tunnel is on the HA.

atmpFASecondaryHAAddress.name: atmpFASecondaryHAAddress
atmpFASecondaryHAAddress.description: The Address of the secondary HA. This is known only on the FA and will be NULL if the tunnel is on the HA.

atmpFASsnStatusIndex.name: atmpFASsnStatusIndex
atmpFASsnStatusIndex.description: The session status entry index. This is used to tie in the tunnel with a mobile node. It is the same as ssnStatusIndex. This is only known on the FA and will be 0 if the tunnel is on the HA.

atmpFAUserName.name: atmpFAUserName
atmpFAUserName.description: The name of the mobile node. This is only known on the FA and will be NULL if the tunnel is on the HA.

atmpInPkts.name: atmpInPkts
atmpInPkts.description: The number of packets received on this tunnel from the peer Agent. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpInOctets.name: atmpInOctets
atmpInOctets.description: The number of octets received on this tunnel from the peer Agent. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpInErrPkts.name: atmpInErrPkts
atmpInErrPkts.description: The number of packets received on this tunnel from the peer Agent that were dropped. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpOutPkts.name: atmpOutPkts
atmpOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent on this tunnel to the peer Agent. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpOutOctets.name: atmpOutOctets
atmpOutOctets.description: The number of octets sent on this tunnel to the peer Agent. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpOutErrPkts.name: atmpOutErrPkts
atmpOutErrPkts.description: The number of packets dropped on this tunnel before sending to peer Agent. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpPktsForcedToFragment.name: atmpPktsForcedToFragment
atmpPktsForcedToFragment.description: The number of packets forced to pre-fragment despite the DF bit. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.

atmpPktsFailedFragment.name: atmpPktsFailedFragment
atmpPktsFailedFragment.description: The number of packets that required to be fragmented but were dropped because atmpAgentForceFragemtnation was disable and the DF bit was set. Not valid for tunnels in local client mode.
